            'If available, the title deeds of the immovable properties to be partitioned, otherwise a document specifying the block and parcel number of the immovable property or the verbal declaration of the owner, Photo identification cards or passports of the co-owners of the immovable properties subject to partition or their authorized representatives, Two passport-sized photographs of each co-owner, 6 x 4 cm in size, taken within the last six months, If one or both parties to the contract are represented by a proxy, a separate document of representation is required. In the case of immovable properties registered as collective ownership (not converted to co-ownership or registered in the name of the deceased), according to the certified partition agreement prepared by a notary public among all heirs of the immovable property owner and bearing the photographs of the heirs, (If the agreement grants the heirs the authority to request registration, each can request the registration of the immovable property allocated to them. If there is no registration authority, all heirs must request registration, or if this is not possible, a court order must be obtained for registration.) For the physical partition of immovable properties under co-ownership among shareholders, by preparing an official deed with the participation of all owners in person or their authorized representatives; in the case of partition by subdivision, by preparing an official deed with the participation of all owners or their authorized representatives, along with the change declaration to be prepared by the cadastre directorates, to meet the demands.',
