            '- Petition: A petition signed by all owners showing the separate values of all independent sections and the land shares allocated to these sections in proportion to their values. - General Construction Project: Must be prepared by an architect or engineer and its accuracy must be approved by the municipality (or by the Directorate of Public Works and Settlement outside municipal boundaries). It is mandatory for each of the multiple buildings constructed on a single plot to be shown separately in the project, and for block buildings, a separate project must be submitted for each block. - Site Plan: For multiple buildings (blocks or separate) to be constructed on a plot, their location within the plot, and any common areas such as private roads, green areas, sports facilities, if any, must be clearly shown and approved by the municipality. If a site plan is included in the general construction project, there is no need to submit a separate site plan. - Management Plan: Every page of the management plan regulating the management of the main real estate must be signed by all owners. - List: The list must show the land share of each independent section, its type such as floor, apartment, office, and their sequential numbers starting from one, and any annexes, and must be signed by the owner or all co-owners of the main real estate and certified by a notary public. - Photo identification cards of the owners or authorized representatives. - Two passport-sized photographs of each owner, 6 x 4 cm in size, taken within the last six months. (For affixing to official deeds and title deeds.)',
