            'Those who wish to carry out transactions at the Cadastre Directorates personally or through their agents (representatives), or if applicable, their legal representatives (proxy, guardian, trustee, and legal advisor), first apply to the cadastre director or an assigned personnel with the necessary documents, stating the type of transaction they wish to carry out. After it is determined that the request comes from the applicant or the interested party of the immovable property, a request document is prepared. Missing documents are noted on the back of the request document, and their completion is ensured. If a date is given for the transaction, a paper with a stamp containing the date and time of the transaction and the cadastral registration number is filled out and given to the applicant. The director refers the requested work to the officer. For plan sample requests, the fee amount specified in Fee Law No. 492 is deposited by the interested party to T.C. Ziraat Bank, Vakıflar Bank, Halk Bank, İş Bank, Yapı ve Kredi Bank, Garanti Bank, Şekerbank, Finansbank A.Ş., Oyakbank A.Ş., or the relevant finance cashier. For other transactions, revolving fund fees are deposited to the relevant bank or the bank account number belonging to the Revolving Fund Enterprise Treasury. Office and field controls and measurements are carried out, and if the work requires it, a registration notification (declaration) is prepared. The declaration is signed by the interested parties and sent to the Land Registry Directorate with a cover letter for registration.',
